M-star


NSTEPS=   1500           !step number (200 recommended for coupling)
IMW=       1         
RSURF=     0.8                
ZY=	   60.     
DTAU0=     0.5
ZCON=      20
P0=        1.e-4
PN2=       1.
PCO2=      1.e-2
G=	   980.         !Gravity (Mars=373., Earth=980., Gliese581d=1744.0, assuming 5.6 earth masses) 
FAC=       4.0
IO3=       0   			!Ozone?
IUP=       1                   !1 means that it starts a new run and doesn't read TempIn.dat
TG0=       250.			!Surface temperature for IUP=1   
TSTRAT=    200.             	!Stratospheric temperature for IUP=1
STARR=     "M3600"		!What star?
ICONSERV=  1           	        !Type of energy conservation
ICOUPLE=   0            	!Coupled(1) or not(0)
SRFALB=    0.27	                !fixed planetary albedo (0.2)
SOLCON=    0.8	  	!SOLCON=S/So (0.3225 = 0.75*0.43)  use 0.43 for present day mars, .2844 for GJ581d,22.49 unscaled
dtmax=     1.e4
CO2MAX=    3.55e-2
IMET=	   0			! Methane flag. If "1" then methane is turned on. 
nga=       1     


Get to 288K, no methane

Surface Pressure (bars) 	Temperature (K)		PALB
1.e-2				278.77    		.2023
3.3e-2				288.04			.1854
	
Optically thinner, so expect more absorption in atmospheres before the anti-greenhouse effect begins..

NOW add methane incrementally as before ( ~288K)
starting from 3.3e-2 bar, 288K
